# Mobile (Flutter)

## File naming — snake_case (always)

Dart/Flutter standard: **snake_case** for every file and folder under `lib/`.

| ✅ Correct | ❌ Wrong |
|-----------|---------|
| `login_screen.dart` | `login-screen.dart`, `LoginScreen.dart`, `cares_login_screen.dart` |
| `app_theme.dart` | `appTheme.dart`, `CaresTheme.dart` |
| `register_face_scan_step.dart` | `registerFaceScanStep.dart` |

- **Files & folders**: `lower_snake_case` only.
- **Classes / enums**: `PascalCase` (`LoginScreen`, `AppColors`).
- **Members / functions**: `lowerCamelCase` (`onComplete`, `buildAppTheme`).
- Do **not** prefix every file/class with `cares` or `Cares`. Reserve product branding for `main.dart` (`CaresApp`), app title, and copy constants.
- Feature paths: `features/auth/presentation/screens/login_screen.dart`.

## Folder layout (required)

```
lib/
├── core/           # constants, theme, utils, network, services
├── shared/         # widgets, components, models (cross-feature)
├── features/
│   └── {feature}/  # auth, face_verification, onboarding, dashboard, settings
│       ├── presentation/
│       ├── data/
│       └── domain/
└── main.dart
```

- New code goes in the correct layer. Do not put feature UI in `core/`.
- Prefer `shared/widgets/` for reusable UI used by 2+ features.

## UI vs logic

```dart
// BAD — API/business logic inside build/onPressed
onPressed: () async { /* 50+ lines */ }

// GOOD — thin widget, logic in controller/notifier
onPressed: ref.read(loginControllerProvider.notifier).login,
```

- **State management: Riverpod** (`flutter_riverpod`). Use `Notifier`/`AsyncNotifier` or `StateNotifier` for feature controllers; expose providers from `presentation/` or `data/`.
- Screens compose widgets; controllers handle async work, validation, and API calls.

## Widgets

- Keep screens **under ~300 lines**. Split into `presentation/widgets/` (feature) or `shared/widgets/` (reusable).
- Reuse shared components: `PrimaryButton`, `CustomTextField`, etc. in `shared/widgets/` — no copy-paste buttons/fields.

## Environment

- Use **`.env`** (e.g. `flutter_dotenv`) for API base URL, keys, tokens.
- Never hardcode URLs, API keys, or secrets in source.

## Dependencies

- Add `flutter_riverpod` (and `flutter_dotenv` when wiring env) via `pubspec.yaml` when introducing state/env — do not invent a second state solution.

## Imports

- Package imports: `package:mobile/...` matching `pubspec.yaml` name `mobile`.
